commit.message:
Keep output as native string so we can compatible with python2 interface

1. open() return string on both python2 and python3, just keep it.
2. stdout of Popen() return string on python2, and bytes on python3,
    decode to string.
Remove space
Fix detection of redhat enterprise compute node
fix bad merge
add MidnightBSD sample uname
Add MidnightBSD support.
#239 fix Oracle Linux 4/5 lsb_release id
#239 Oracle Enterprise Linux was renamed to Oracle Linux since version 5.x

Ignore /etc/plesk-release file while parsing distribution

Signed-off-by: Abhijeet Kasurde <akasurde@redhat.com>

Prefer mapping to JSON string as test expectation

This is easier to read and maintain and more resilient to formatting
changes.

Reported-by: Sebastian Pipping <sebastian@pipping.org>
Signed-off-by: Philippe Ombredanne <pombredanne@nexb.com>

Use explicit named keyword arguments and values in tests

Using explicit named arguments when creating a LinuxDistribution makes
the tests more readable than using positional unnamed arguments.

Using 'path-to-non-existing-file' as a variable value for non-existing
test file paths is easier to understand than a terse 'non' value.

Reported-by: Sebastian Pipping <sebastian@pipping.org>
Signed-off-by: Philippe Ombredanne <pombredanne@nexb.com>
